# {{.ProjectName}}

Connect an online service with one plugin repo, then generate the supported outputs you need.

This starter uses job-first language on purpose:

- primary path: connect an online service
- technical shape: hosted MCP without launcher code
- edit only `src/`

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai inspect . --authoring
plugin-kit-ai generate .
plugin-kit-ai generate --check .
{{- if .PrimaryTarget }}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform {{.PrimaryTarget}} --strict
{{- else }}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
{{- end }}
```

Then validate any other supported output you plan to ship.

## Editable Source

- `src/plugin.yaml`: shared plugin identity and supported outputs
- `src/mcp/servers.yaml`: your online service connection
- root `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`: boundary docs that point humans and agents back to `src/`

